SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 457
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Cadet Josh Stoll upon
his selection for a Judge Advocate General
internship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those exemplary individuals who, through their academic excellence and dedication to service,
bring honor to the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Cadet Josh Stoll, a student at Carson-Newman University and a member of
the school's U.S. Army ROTC Eagle Battalion, has been selected for a competitive Judge
Advocate General (JAG) internship for the summer of 2025; and
WHEREAS, currently one of the program's MS4s, Cadet Stoll has demonstrated
outstanding leadership in his roles as S2, S3 Future Operations, and currently as S5, where he
oversees media responsibilities for the battalion; and
WHEREAS, a native of Summertown, Josh Stoll is pursuing a degree in political science
at Carson-Newman University and plans to continue his education at the Lincoln Memorial
University Duncan School of Law, with aspirations of serving his country through the legal
profession; and
WHEREAS, the JAG internship program offers invaluable experience in military legal
affairs, and Cadet Stoll's selection is a testament to his exceptional qualifications and
commitment to the principles of justice and service; and
WHEREAS, Josh Stoll's achievement reflects the high standards of Carson-Newman
University and its ROTC program and serves as an inspiration to his peers and future cadets;
and
