WHEREAS, Cadet Stoll is an impressive young man who exemplifies the values of
leadership, dedication, and excellence, and it is fitting that he be recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Cadet Josh Stoll upon his
selection to the Judge Advocate General internship program, extend our congratulations on this
significant accomplishment, and offer our best wishes for much continued success in his future
endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
